{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-post-index-js","path":"/static-site-with-docker-and-nginx","webpackCompilationHash":"8d2ec58451660e93ed4c","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you need a quick way to serve static files, Nginx with Docker Compose is a\nhassle free alternative:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yaml\"><pre class=\"language-yaml\"><code class=\"language-yaml\"><span class=\"token comment\"># docker-compose.yml</span>\n<span class=\"token key atrule\">nginx</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"token key atrule\">image</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> nginx\n  <span class=\"token key atrule\">volumes</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n   <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> ./public<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>/usr/share/nginx/html\n  <span class=\"token key atrule\">ports</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n   <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"80:80\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Just need to create a <code class=\"language-text\">public</code> folder as a sibling to the <code class=\"language-text\">docker-compose.yml</code>\nand create the <code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> there.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"August 18, 2019","path":"/static-site-with-docker-and-nginx","title":"Static site with Docker and Nginx"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false}}}